==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Severance
<hw>Sev"er*ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of severing, or the state of being severed; partition;
separation.</def> <rj><au>Milman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The act of dividing; the singling
or severing of two or more that join, or are joined, in one writ; the
putting in several or separate pleas or answers by two or more
disjointly; the destruction of the unity of interest in a joint
estate.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Severe</ent>⟦br⟧
